===Noun===
{{en-noun|!}}

# {{context|obsolete|sometimes used|_|abusively|lang=en}} One born illegitimately (''i.e.'', out of {{l/en|wedlock}}); a {{l/en|bastard}}.
# {{context|loosely|quasi-nominal collective|as “the misbegotten ''[''are'']''”|lang=en}} That set of people born into {{l/en|infelicitous}} circumstances.
#* '''1973''', {{w|Philippa Foot}}, “Nietzsche: The Revaluation of Values” in ''Nietzsche: A Collection of Critical Essays'', edited by {{w|Robert C. Solomon}}, {{w|Garden City, New York}}: [[w:Doubleday (publisher)|Anchor Books]], ISBN 0385033443, page 161:
#*: By preserving the incapable and “'''misbegotten'''”, and by insisting that they be the object of compassionate attention, it would cause even the strong to be infected with gloom and nihilism.

